{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Tutorial: How to Create a Part Picker Form","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>In this tutorial we&#x2019;re going to be making a parts builder form. It&#x2019;s an extension of the <a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/shopify-tutorial-order-form/\">Order Form</a> that I created a while back. It works by listing single-option products in a table with each variant listed as a radio button. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://stroman-nolan491.myshopify.com/pages/order-form-2\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 57.58483033932136%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image \" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"parts builder\" title src=\"/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/dbb61/parts-builder.png\" srcset=\"/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/19bd1/parts-builder.png 163w,\n/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/d3bcb/parts-builder.png 325w,\n/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/dbb61/parts-builder.png 650w,\n/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/6b691/parts-builder.png 975w,\n/static/8de09129bfca088fb1b4a41f82669489/77c37/parts-builder.png 1002w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<p>You can see a demo <a href=\"https://stroman-nolan491.myshopify.com/pages/order-form-2\">here</a>.</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Create a new linklist</h2>\n<p>The first thing you want to do is create a linklist that holds the products that you want to sell through the order form. Go to the &#x201C;Navigation&#x201D; page of your admin, and create a new linklist called &#x201C;Part Picker&#x201D;. Next, add links to the products that you want to have listed on the order form. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/part-picker-link-list.png\"><img src=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/part-picker-link-list.png\" alt=\"part picker link list\" width=\"944\" height=\"490\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2628\"></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">The products that you enter in this linklist will be shown in the table that we&#x2019;re going to create in the next step.</div>\n<p>Please keep in mind that you can only use <strong>single-option products</strong>.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Create an alternate page template</h2>\n<p>In your Template Editor, click &#x201C;add a new template&#x201D; under the Templates section. Select &#x201C;page&#x201D;, and call it &#x201C;part-picker&#x201D;.  </p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/576cc/part-picker-template.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 83.59375000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-2632\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"part picker template\" title src=\"/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/dbb61/part-picker-template.png\" srcset=\"/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/19bd1/part-picker-template.png 163w,\n/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/d3bcb/part-picker-template.png 325w,\n/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/dbb61/part-picker-template.png 650w,\n/static/d1bd7ea2627a99f7b4d53f8c6cdcff79/576cc/part-picker-template.png 896w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<p>Copy the code from this <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/raw/4409175/27c1f5e2cfb26202ef79d434aaa68733969ed745/gistfile1.txt\">gist</a> and paste it in page.part-picker.liquid. Hit save. It&#x2019;s pretty bare-bones, and there&#x2019;s a bit of inline CSS so you&#x2019;ll have to pretty it up a bit.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Create a new page for your part picker</h2>\n<p>Go to Blogs &amp; Pages, and create a new Page. You can title it whatever you wish. The important part here is to tell it to use the freshly-created page.part-picker.liquid template. You do this by selecting it under the &#x201C;Templates&#x201D; dropdown, shown below:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/59146/part-picker-template-page.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 64.60446247464503%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-2636\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"part picker template page\" title src=\"/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/dbb61/part-picker-template-page.png\" srcset=\"/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/19bd1/part-picker-template-page.png 163w,\n/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/d3bcb/part-picker-template-page.png 325w,\n/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/dbb61/part-picker-template-page.png 650w,\n/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/6b691/part-picker-template-page.png 975w,\n/static/434cc5c04b356f8ec5050e0875d244c7/59146/part-picker-template-page.png 986w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Add the part picker script</h2>\n<p>Inside your Template Editor, create a new snippet called &#x201C;parts-picker-script&#x201D;. Add the contents of <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/raw/4409215/794c304183a319111350b562dcf75cf66bfb4ccf/gistfile1.txt\">this gist</a> inside it. </p>\n<p>Place the following code right before the &lt;/body&gt; tag in theme.liquid.</p>\n<pre><code>\n{% include &apos;parts-picker-script&apos; %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<h2 class=\"step\">The End</h2>\n<p>That&#x2019;s it that&#x2019;s all! You will likely need to sprinkle some CSS love on your table to make it fit in with your theme. </p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-tutorial-how-to-create-a-part-picker-form"}}